Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.29,0:00:08.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}曾经有一个世界\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Once there was a world
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.42,0:00:11.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它与我们的星球没什么不同\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}not so very different from our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.10,0:00:24.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}偶尔会有些自然灾害或者是大规模的火山爆发\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There were occasional natural catastrophes, massive volcanic eruptions
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.98,0:00:29.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}时不时还会有小行星降临在星球上砸几个坑\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and, every once in a while, an asteroid would come barreling out of the blue to do some damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.42,0:00:28.15,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.86,0:00:32.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可在最初的100万年里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But for the first billion years or so,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.61,0:00:37.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它很像是一个天堂\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it would've seemed like a paradise.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.32,0:00:42.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这大概就是金星在太阳系还年轻时的样子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is what we think the planet Venus might have looked like when our solar system was young.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.25,0:00:48.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}然后 一切就开始变得糟糕了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Then things started to go horribly wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.99,0:02:32.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\fe134}{\fsp0}{\fad(500,500)}{\pos(190,278)}{\fn方正准圆简体}{\bord0}{\fs20}{\c&H24EFFF&}宇宙大探索\N{\fs17}{\c&HFFFFFF&} 第十二集
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.92,0:02:54.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}金星或许曾是一个天堂\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The planet Venus, which once may have seemed like a heaven,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.59,0:02:56.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但现在却是一个地狱\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}turned into a kind of hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.42,0:02:59.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}造成这个差异的原因是因为有一些微妙的自然平衡被打破了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The difference between the two can be a delicate balance,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.72,0:03:02.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而且是比你想象中更为微妙的关系\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}far more delicate than you might imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.18,0:03:06.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这个平衡一旦被打破 就再也无法挽回\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Once things began to unravel, there was no way back.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.06,0:03:08.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是金星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is what Venus,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.93,0:03:11.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}距离我们最近的行星 今天看上去的样子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our nearest planetary neighbor, looks like today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.11,0:03:25.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}金星上的海洋已经消失很久了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Venus's oceans are long gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.53,0:03:27.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}星球的表面现在比烧烤炉还要烫\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The surface is hotter than a broiling oven,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.30,0:03:29.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}热得足以融化铅\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}hot enough to melt lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.96,0:03:32.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为什么呢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.17,0:03:36.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你也许认为这是因为金星到太阳的距离要比地球少30%\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You might think it's because Venus is 30% closer to the Sun than the Earth is,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.38,0:03:38.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但这不是真正的原因\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but that's not the reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.88,0:03:42.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}金星现在完全被硫酸云覆盖着\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Venus is completely covered by clouds of sulfuric acid
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.51,0:03:45.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}几乎没有阳光可以照射到它的表面\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that keep almost all the sunlight from reaching the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.89,0:03:48.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}按理来说这应该让金星比地球更寒冷\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That ought to make Venus much colder than the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.89,0:03:51.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但为何金星会如此的灼热？\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So why is Venus scorching hot?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.83,0:03:53.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那是因为有小部分的阳光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's because the small amount of sunlight
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.96,0:03:57.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}穿过云层抵达了地面\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that trickles in through the clouds to reach the surface
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.03,0:03:59.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}却没能反射回去\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}can't get back out again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.17,0:04:02.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}能量不能散发是由于浓密的大气阻隔\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The flow of energy is blocked by a dense atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.04,0:04:03.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那就是二氧化碳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of carbon dioxide.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.70,0:04:07.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}二氧化碳简称CO2\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That carbon dioxide gas-- or CO2 for short--
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.68,0:04:10.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它就像毯子一样阻止热量的散发\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}acts like a smothering blanket to keep the heat in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.01,0:04:12.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没人在金星上烧煤\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No one is burning coal
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.81,0:04:15.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}或是开着大马力的汽车在上面逛\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or driving big gas-guzzlers on Venus.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.48,0:04:17.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}自然能灭掉环境的平衡\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Nature can destroy an environment
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.35,0:04:20.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而不需要借助人的力量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}without any help from intelligent life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.09,0:04:24.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}金星现在正处于强烈的温室效应中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Venus is in the grip of a runaway greenhouse effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.69,0:04:28.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为什么我们现在像是在一个碗里？\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Why does it look like we're inside a bowl?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.60,0:04:31.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那是因为浓密的大气压力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's due to the intense atmospheric pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.53,0:04:36.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是金星13号的残骸\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's the wreck of Venera 13.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.44,0:04:39.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1982年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In 1982, the scientists and engineers
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.17,0:04:41.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}苏联的科学家与工程师们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of what was then the Soviet Union
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.58,0:04:44.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}成功地将这艘探测器送到了金星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}successfully landed this spacecraft on Venus.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.38,0:04:46.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们设法让飞船\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They managed to keep it refrigerated
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.61,0:04:48.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}保持了2个小时以上的冷冻状态\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for overtwo hours,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.35,0:04:51.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}让它能给四周拍照\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so it could photograph its surroundings...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.29,0:04:54.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并将照片传回了地球\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and transmit the images back to Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.79,0:04:58.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}随后飞船上的电子设备就烧毁了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}before the on-board electronics were fried.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.93,0:05:07.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}金星与地球在诞生初期具有相同的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Venus and Earth started out with about the same amount
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.40,0:05:10.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}碳含量 但两个星球却被推上了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of carbon, but the two worlds were propelled
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.20,0:05:12.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}截然不同的发展道路\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}along radically different paths,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.57,0:05:16.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}碳元素在其中起到了决定性的作用\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and carbon was the decisive element in both stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.08,0:05:20.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在金星 几乎所有的大气\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On Venus, it's almost all in the form of gas--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.15,0:05:23.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都由二氧化碳组成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}carbon dioxide-- in the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.49,0:05:30.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球上大部分的碳已经在久远的年代中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most of the carbon on Earth has been stored for eons
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.49,0:05:33.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以碳酸盐岩的形式被储存起来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in solid vaults of carbonate rock,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.26,0:05:35.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就像这一块 它就是其中一种形式\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like this one, part of a chain that forms
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.77,0:05:38.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是著名的多佛海岸白色悬崖\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the celebrated White Cliffs of Dover,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.53,0:05:40.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它位于英吉利海峡的边上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}right on the English Channel.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.87,0:05:44.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是哪位巨人修建了这样的世界奇观？\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What titan built this wonder of the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.06,0:06:04.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那是一种比针头还要小1000倍的生物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A creature a thousand times smaller than a pinhead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.56,0:06:06.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}数以万亿计\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Trillions of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.57,0:06:09.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它叫单细胞藻类\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One-celled algae.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.87,0:06:17.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}火山将二氧化碳送入大气后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Volcanoes supply carbon dioxide to the atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.24,0:06:20.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}海洋将它缓慢地吸收\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the oceans slowly absorb it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.45,0:06:23.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这个过程要延续好几百万年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Working over the course of millions of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.12,0:06:26.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}先是微小的藻类吸收了二氧化碳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the microscopic algae harvested the carbon dioxide
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.29,0:06:28.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并将它转化为这些小贝壳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and turned it into these tiny shells.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.02,0:06:31.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}日积月累 最终沉积为白垩\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They accumulated in thick deposits of chalk,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.56,0:06:34.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们也称之为石灰岩 它积聚在海床上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or limestone, on the ocean floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.23,0:06:41.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}最终 永不停息的地壳运动将海床推起\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Later, the restless Earth pushed up the sea floor
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.63,0:06:45.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将它塑造成这些巨大的悬崖\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and carved out these massive cliffs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.97,0:06:48.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}其它的海洋生物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Other marine creatures
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.11,0:06:51.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}用二氧化碳建造了巨大的珊瑚礁\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}took in carbon dioxide to build enormous coral reefs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.91,0:06:55.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}海洋也可以把溶解的二氧化碳转换为石灰岩\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the oceans converted dissolved CO2 into limestone
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.88,0:06:57.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而不需要生物的帮助\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}even without any help from life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.95,0:07:01.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}最终 只有微量的二氧化碳气体\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As a result, only a trace amount was left as a gas
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.59,0:07:03.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}留在了地球的大气中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in Earth's atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.12,0:07:06.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还不到每百分之一中的三百分之一\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Not even three-hundredths of one percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.26,0:07:09.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}相当于每1万个分子中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Think of it-- fewer than three molecules
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.26,0:07:12.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只有不到3个分子保留下来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}out of every ten thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.40,0:07:17.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而这几个分子就是最关键的因素\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And yet, it makes the critical difference
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.84,0:07:22.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}决定了地球是生命的乐土还是荒芜之地\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}between a barren wasteland and a garden of life on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.98,0:07:25.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}要是一点二氧化碳都没有\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With no CO2 at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.95,0:07:29.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球将会被冰冻\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Earth would be frozen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.78,0:07:31.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可要是二氧化碳的数量再多一倍\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And with twice as many,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.82,0:07:33.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也就是像前面所说的 每1万个分子中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we're still talking about only six molecules
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.79,0:07:35.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有6个分子保留下来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}out of ten thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.42,0:07:37.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}令人不安的炎热就会袭来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Things would get uncomfortably hot
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.52,0:07:40.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}给人类带来一系列的问题\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and cause us some serious problems...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.39,0:07:44.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不过还不会像金星那么热 一点都不会\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but never as hot as Venus; not even close.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.13,0:07:46.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在好几百万年前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That planet lost its ocean to space
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.83,0:07:48.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这个行星上的海洋就已经消失到太空中了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}billions of years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.17,0:07:51.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没有了海洋 它就没有办法从空气中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Without an ocean, it had no way to capture CO2
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.41,0:07:54.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}捕获二氧化碳 并将它存储为矿物质\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from the atmosphere and store it as a mineral.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.13,0:07:56.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从喷发的火山中产生的二氧化碳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The CO2 from erupting volcanoes
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.28,0:07:58.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不断地积累\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just continued to build up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.95,0:08:02.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}时至今日 金星上的大气要比地球重90倍\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Today, that atmosphere is 90 times heavier than ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.35,0:08:05.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}几乎全部由灼热的二氧化碳气体组成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Almost all of it is heat-trapping carbon dioxide.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.72,0:08:09.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是为什么金星会变成如此残酷的地狱\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's why Venus is such a ferocious inferno
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.09,0:08:12.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}生命无法在此扎根的原因\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so hostile to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.73,0:08:15.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球则恰恰与此相反\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Earth, in stunning contrast,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.90,0:08:17.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它是有生命的星球\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.60,0:08:20.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它会呼吸\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It breathes...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.20,0:08:22.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不过很缓慢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but very slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.44,0:08:24.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1年才能完成1次呼吸\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A single breath takes a whole year.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.78,0:08:27.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}森林里包含了地球上大部分的生命\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The forests contain most of Earth's life,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.08,0:08:29.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大部分的森林都位于北半球\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and most forests are in the Northern Hemisphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.98,0:08:32.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当北半球的春季到来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When spring comes to the north,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.15,0:08:35.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}森林吸入空气中的二氧化碳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the forests inhale carbon dioxide from the air
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.22,0:08:38.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并随之生长 将大地铺满绿色\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and grow, turning the land green.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.42,0:08:41.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大气中的二氧化碳含量随之下降\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The amount of CO2 in the atmosphere goes down.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.49,0:08:46.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}秋天降临 植物落叶 随之枯萎\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When fall comes and the plants drop their leaves, they decay,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.06,0:08:49.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将二氧化碳呼出到大气中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}exhaling the carbon dioxide back into the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.00,0:08:52.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}同样的过程也会发生在南半球\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The same thing happens in the Southern Hemisphere
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.64,0:08:54.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只是季节是相反的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at the opposite time of the year.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.97,0:08:57.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但南半球大部分是海洋\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the Southern Hemisphere is mostly ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.98,0:08:59.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因此 是北半球的森林\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So it's the forests of the north
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.01,0:09:03.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}控制了全球每年二氧化碳含量的变化\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that control the annual changes in the global CO2.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.51,0:09:05.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球已经像这样呼吸了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Earth has been breathing like this
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.32,0:09:06.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}数千万年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for tens of millions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.45,0:09:10.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从没有人注意到这一点 直到1958年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But nobody noticed until 1958,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.42,0:09:13.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有一位海洋学家叫查尔斯?戴维?基林\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when an oceanographer named Charles David Keeling
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.59,0:09:14.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他设计了一种方法 可以精确地测量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}devised a way to accurately measure
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.63,0:09:17.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}空气中二氧化碳的含量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the amount of carbon dioxide in the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.97,0:09:21.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}基林发现了地球的细微呼吸\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Keeling discovered the Earth's exquisite respiration.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.81,0:09:28.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但他也发现了一些令人震惊的事实\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But he also discovered something shocking--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.35,0:09:31.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有一个数字在以人类历史上前所未有的速度上升\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a rapid rise, unprecedented in human history,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.02,0:09:34.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那就是空气中二氧化碳的整体水平\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the overall level of CO2,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.59,0:09:36.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}至今这个变化还一直在继续\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one that has continued ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.43,0:09:46.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}二氧化碳水平的惊人变化\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a striking departure from the CO2 levels that prevailed
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.97,0:09:50.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}始于农业与文明的兴起时期\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}during the rise of agriculture and civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.27,0:09:53.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}实际上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In fact, the Earth has seen nothing like it
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.84,0:09:57.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球在过去的300万年不是这个样子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for three million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.31,0:10:00.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们为何如此确信\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&} How can we be so sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.21,0:10:04.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}证据就记录在水里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The evidence is written in water.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.65,0:10:14.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球保存着一份详细的日记\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Earth keeps a detailed diary
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.62,0:10:16.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它就写在过去下的雪里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}written in the snows of yesteryear.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.96,0:10:19.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}气候科学家们钻出冰芯\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Climate scientists have drilled ice cores
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.00,0:10:23.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从格林兰岛和南极洲的冰川深处\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from the depths of glaciers in Greenland and Antarctica.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.67,0:10:28.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}远古的空气被困在了冰层里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The ice layers have ancient air trapped inside them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.17,0:10:32.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们可以阅读到地球大气的完整记录\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We can read the unbroken record of Earth's atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.78,0:10:36.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一直可以追溯到8万年前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that extends back over the last 800,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.25,0:10:38.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在以往的所有时间内\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In all that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.52,0:10:41.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大气中的二氧化碳数值从没有超过\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the amount of carbon dioxide in the air never rose
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.12,0:10:43.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每百分之一的空气中含有三百分之一的二氧化碳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}above three-hundredths of one percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.42,0:10:47.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但到了二十世纪\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That is, until the turn of the 20th century.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.19,0:10:50.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它就开始稳定而迅速的上升并保持至今\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it's been going up steadily and rapidly ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.40,0:10:52.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}现在这个数值\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's now more than 40% higher
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.93,0:10:55.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}已经比工业革命前高出了40%\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than before the Industrial Revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.20,0:10:58.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}通过燃烧煤 石油和煤气\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By burning coal, oil and gas,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.40,0:11:01.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人类文明在释放出二氧化碳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our civilization is exhaling carbon dioxide
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.74,0:11:04.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}远远超过了地球所能吸收的速度\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}much faster than Earth can absorb it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.04,0:11:07.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因此大气中的二氧化碳在不断积累\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So CO2 is building up in the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.55,0:11:09.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这个星球在升温\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The planet is heating up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.78,0:11:14.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每一个发热的物体都能辐射出某种我们肉眼看不见的光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every warm object radiates a kind of light we can't see with the naked eye--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.89,0:11:16.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那就是热红外线\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}thermal infrared light.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.79,0:11:21.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}即使在黑暗中 我们的身体也能散发出不可见的热辐射\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We all glow with invisible heat radiation, even in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.33,0:11:25.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果用红外线观察地球 它就是这个样子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is what the Earth looks like in the infrared.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.26,0:11:30.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你看到的是行星本身的发热\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You're seeing the planet's own body heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.07,0:11:37.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当阳光照射到地面\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Incoming light from the Sun hits the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.81,0:11:40.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球本身会吸收大部分的能量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Earth absorbs much of that energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.25,0:11:41.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}让地球升温\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which heats the planet up
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.01,0:11:46.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从而让地表发出红外线\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and makes the surface glow in infrared light.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.08,0:11:48.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但空气中的二氧化碳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the carbon dioxide in the atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.49,0:11:51.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}又会吸收散发出的大部分热量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}absorbs most of that outgoing heat radiation,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.36,0:11:54.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}把这些热量的大部分又传回地面\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sending much of it right back to the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.16,0:11:57.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}让地球变得更热\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This makes the planet even warmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.26,0:11:59.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是所谓的温室效应\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's all there is to the greenhouse effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.60,0:12:01.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它的基本物理原理\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's basic physics,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.27,0:12:03.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就在于把流动的能量保存下来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just bookkeeping of the energy flow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.67,0:12:06.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}关于它没什么好争议的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's nothing controversial about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.37,0:12:09.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果大气中一点二氧化碳都没有\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If we didn't have any carbon dioxide in our atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.27,0:12:12.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球就会变成一个大雪球\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Earth would just be a great big snowball,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.44,0:12:14.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人类也就不会存在\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we wouldn't be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.05,0:12:19.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因此 轻度的温室效应是件好事\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, a little greenhouse effect is a good thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.82,0:12:22.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可它要是变大 就会造成气候的不稳定\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But a big one can destabilize the climate
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.92,0:12:25.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}甚至毁掉人类的生存方式\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and wreck our way of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.06,0:12:29.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}好吧 但我们怎么知道人类是问题的根源？\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All right... but how do we know that we're the problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.16,0:12:32.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也许是地球本身导致二氧化碳的增加\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Maybe the Earth itself is causing the rise in CO2.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.00,0:12:36.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也许和煤与石油的燃烧无关\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Maybe it has nothing to do with the coal and oil we burn.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.40,0:12:38.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}或许是那些该死的火山\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Maybe it's those damn volcanoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.74,0:12:44.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每隔几年 西西里岛的埃特纳火山就会喷发\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every few years, Mount Etna, in Sicily, blows its stack.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.01,0:12:48.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每次的大规模喷发都会把几百万吨二氧化碳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Each big eruption sends millions of tons of CO2
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.88,0:12:50.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}送入空气\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.78,0:12:53.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果我们把\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, combine that with the output
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.29,0:12:56.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球上所有的火山喷发合计起来的话\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of all the other volcanic activity on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.62,0:12:59.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}让我们按最大数量进行科学预测\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Let's take the largest scientific estimate--
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.79,0:13:03.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每年大概会有5亿吨二氧化碳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about 500 million tons of volcanic CO2
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.63,0:13:05.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}被送入空气中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}entering the atmosphere ever year.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.80,0:13:08.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}听上去很多 对不对？\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Sounds like a lot, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.57,0:13:13.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可这个数值还不到人类每年产生的二氧化碳数量的2%\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But that's not even two percent of the 30 billion tons of CO2
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.10,0:13:16.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那就是1年300亿吨\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that our civilization is cranking out every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.14,0:13:18.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而且 还有个很有趣的现象\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And, funny thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.04,0:13:21.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大气中二氧化碳的增加量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the measured increase in CO2 in the atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.91,0:13:25.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}与我们所知的 即是通过燃烧煤 石油和煤气产生的二氧化碳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}tallies with the known amount we're dumping there
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.78,0:13:29.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}刚好相同\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by burning coal, oil and gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.79,0:13:32.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}火山产生的二氧化碳有一个明显的特征\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Volcanic CO2 has a distinct signature--
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.89,0:13:34.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}与化石燃料燃烧时产生的二氧化碳相比\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's slightly heavier than the kind produced
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.56,0:13:36.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它要稍微重一些\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by burning fossil fuels.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.96,0:13:38.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们可以分辨出这两者的差别\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We can tell the difference between the two
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.83,0:13:41.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}通过对它们进行原子级别的检验\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when we examine them at the atomic level.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.47,0:13:44.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}检验结果很明显证实 空气中增加的二氧化碳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's clear that the increased CO2 in the air
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.07,0:13:46.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不是来自火山\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is not from volcanoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.34,0:13:49.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}更重要的是 气候变暖的程度与\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What's more, the observed warming is as much as predicted
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.67,0:13:51.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}空气中二氧化碳增加的程度差不多\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from the measured increase in carbon dioxide.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.81,0:13:53.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这两者紧密关联\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a pretty tight case.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.75,0:13:56.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人类排放二氧化碳的证据都在这上面\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our fingerprints are all over this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.28,0:14:00.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每年30亿吨二氧化碳到底有多少?\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How much is 30 billion tons of CO2 per year?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.69,0:14:03.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果我们把它压成一个固体\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you compressed it into solid form,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.15,0:14:05.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它的体积就会和\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it would occupy about the same volume
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.29,0:14:07.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}多佛海岸的白色悬崖差不多\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as the White Cliffs of Dover.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.66,0:14:12.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是我们每年排放到空气中的二氧化碳的数量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we're adding that much CO2 to the air every year,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.10,0:14:14.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}永无休止 年复一年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}relentlessly, year after year.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.67,0:14:17.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}很不幸的是\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Unlucky for us, the main waste product
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.87,0:14:21.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人类文明产生的主要垃圾产品不是物质\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of our civilization is not just any substance.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.31,0:14:24.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而是能对全球气候调节产生\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It happens to be the chief climate-regulating gas
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.84,0:14:27.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}恒温效果的毒气 年年如此\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of our global thermostat, year in, year out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.55,0:14:31.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}过多的二氧化碳就相当于看不见的毒气\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Too bad CO2 is an invisible gas.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.92,0:14:34.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果我们能看到它……\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Maybe if we could see it...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.56,0:14:37.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果我们的眼睛能感应到二氧化碳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If our eyes were sensitive to CO2--
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.76,0:14:40.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也许在宇宙中有这样的生物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and perhaps there are such beings in the cosmos--
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.76,0:14:44.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果我们能看见二氧化碳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if we could see all that carbon dioxide,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.23,0:14:47.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那就没有人能否定这一切\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then we would overcome the denial
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.27,0:14:50.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并充分了解到人类对大气的严重影响\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and grasp the magnitude of our impact on the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.09,0:15:08.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但全球变暖的证据\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the evidence that the world is getting warmer
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.32,0:15:10.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就在我们身边\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is all around us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.26,0:15:13.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}首先让我们检查一下\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For starters, let's just check the thermometers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.36,0:15:15.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}世界各地气象站的温度计\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Weather stations around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.36,0:15:17.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}自1880年代起\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have been keeping reliable temperature records
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.33,0:15:19.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们一直保存着可靠的温度记录\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}since the 1880s,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.03,0:15:22.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}美国宇航局用这些数据编制了一幅地图\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and NASA has used the data to compile a map
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.17,0:15:23.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地图涵盖了所有的时间段\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}tracking the average temperatures
