Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.18,0:20:54.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每一次都是受某种全球性力量作用的结果\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but always in response to a global force.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.85,0:20:58.15,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}现在影响气候变化最强的力量就是\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The strongest force driving climate change right now
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.19,0:21:01.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}由于燃烧化石燃料而不断增加的二氧化碳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is the increasing CO2 from the burning of fossil fuels,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.19,0:21:03.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它留住了更多的太阳热量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is trapping more heat from the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.53,0:21:06.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些多出来的能量必须有个去处\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All that additional energy has to go somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.36,0:21:08.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有些能量让空气升温\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some of it warms the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.20,0:21:10.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大部分的能量则被海洋吸收\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most of it ends up in the oceans.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.30,0:21:14.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}全世界的海洋现在都在变暖\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All over the world, the oceans are getting warmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.57,0:21:16.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}最明显的就是北冰洋\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's most obvious in the Arctic Ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.01,0:21:19.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以及它周围的陆地\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the lands that surround it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.48,0:21:25.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}好吧 如果说我们正在失去一些夏季的海冰\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Okay, so we're losing the summer sea ice
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.48,0:21:29.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不过那个地方又是没什么人去的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in a place where hardly anyone ever goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.08,0:21:32.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我干嘛要关心北极有没有冰呢？\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What do I care if there's no ice around the North Pole?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.83,0:21:44.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}冰是地球最亮的自然表面\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ice is the brightest natural surface on the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.83,0:21:47.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}广阔的海洋则是最暗的自然表面\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and open ocean water is the darkest.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.77,0:21:51.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}冰能把阳光反射回太空\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Ice reflects incoming sunlight back to space.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.37,0:21:53.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}水则会吸收阳光而变暖\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Water absorbs sunlight
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.44,0:21:56.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这会让更多的冰融化\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and gets warmer, which melts even more ice,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.78,0:22:00.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}让更多的海洋水面暴露出来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which exposes still more ocean surface
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.05,0:22:02.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并吸收更多的阳光\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to absorb even more sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.05,0:22:05.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是所谓的正反馈效应\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is what we call a positive feedback loop.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.52,0:22:09.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是能把二氧化碳引起的热效应放大的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's one of many natural mechanisms that magnify
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.29,0:22:12.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}许多种自然机制中的一个\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}any warming caused by CO2 alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.43,0:22:14.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们现在是在阿拉斯加的德鲁角\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're at Drew Point, Alaska,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.70,0:22:19.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这里是北冰洋的边缘\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the edge of the Arctic Ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.30,0:22:33.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当我出生的时候 这里的海岸线伸出去有1英里多\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When I was born, the shoreline was a mile farther out,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.20,0:22:37.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它过去曾以每年20英尺的速度缩减\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it was breaking off at a rate of about 20 feet per year.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.24,0:22:39.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}现在……\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.24,0:22:43.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}缩减的速度达到了每年50英尺\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's being eaten away at about 50 feet per year.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.41,0:22:45.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}北冰洋正在变暖\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Arctic Ocean is warming
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.41,0:22:47.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而且变暖的速度在不断增快\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and at an increasing rate.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.78,0:22:50.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所以每年里有大部分时间这里是没有冰的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So it's ice-free during more of the year.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.88,0:22:52.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有更多的海岸线因此暴露出来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That leaves the shore here
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.89,0:22:55.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}被风暴所侵蚀\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}more exposed to erosion from storms,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.42,0:22:57.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这让另一种力量变得更强大\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which are also getting more powerful,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.76,0:23:00.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这种力量能影响气候的变化\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}another effect of climate change.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.96,0:23:03.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}阿拉斯加北部 西伯利亚 加拿大\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The northern reaches of Alaska, Siberia and Canada
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.96,0:23:05.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些地方的大部分是永久性冻土\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are mostly permafrost,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.83,0:23:09.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地面被冻结超过千年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ground that has been frozen year-round for millennia.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.27,0:23:11.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它里面含有很多有机质\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It contains lots of organic matter,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.10,0:23:13.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}过去的树叶与树根\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}old leaves and roots from plants
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.84,0:23:16.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们曾生长在数千年前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that grew thousands of years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.01,0:23:18.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}由于北冰洋地区的升温速度在加快\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because the Arctic regions are warming faster
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.01,0:23:20.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}比地球上其它地区都要快\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than anywhere else on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.95,0:23:22.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}永久性冻土开始融化\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the permafrost is thawing
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.02,0:23:25.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}冻土中的东西开始腐烂\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and its contents are rotting,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.02,0:23:28.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}效果就和冰箱断电差不多\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just like when you unplug the freezer.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.53,0:23:34.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}融化的冻土释放出二氧化碳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The thawing permafrost is releasing carbon dioxide
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.96,0:23:38.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有甲烷 这是一种更厉害的的温室气体\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and methane, an even more potent greenhouse gas,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.53,0:23:40.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们都进入了大气中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.30,0:23:42.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这让世界变得更热\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is making things even warmer,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.70,0:23:46.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有一个正反馈效应的例子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}another example of a positive feedback mechanism.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.37,0:23:49.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}世界的永久性冻土层中储存有大量的碳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The world's permafrost stores enough carbon
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.14,0:23:52.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}足以让大气中的二氧化碳再增加一倍\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to more than double the CO2 in the atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.71,0:23:54.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}按照现在的速度\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At the rate we're going,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.05,0:23:55.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}全球变暖很快就要实现大部分了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}global warming could release most of it
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.65,0:23:57.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}时间就是本世纪末\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by the end of the century.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.38,0:24:00.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人类也许正在将气候推上一条不归路\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We might be tipping the climate past a point of no return
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.82,0:24:03.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}让它走向无法预知的一面\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into an unpredictable slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.46,0:24:06.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}好吧 如果空气 水 陆地\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Okay, the air, the water
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.29,0:24:08.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有其它的一切都变暖了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the land are all getting warmer,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.63,0:24:11.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}全球变暖真的发生了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so global warming is really happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.47,0:24:13.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也许这不是人类的错\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But maybe it's not our fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.63,0:24:15.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也许这是自然造成的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Maybe it's just nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.70,0:24:17.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也许是因为太阳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Maybe it's the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.21,0:24:22.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不 也许不是因为太阳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No, it's not the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.31,0:24:26.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们这几十年来一直在密切的观测太阳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We've been monitoring the Sun very closely for decades,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.65,0:24:29.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而太阳输送的能量一直都没有变过\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the solar energy output hasn't changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.49,0:24:33.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有 地球现在是\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What's more, the Earth is warming more at night
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.32,0:24:35.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}晚上比白天更暖\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than in daytime,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.49,0:24:38.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}冬天比夏天更暖\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and more in winter than in summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.33,0:24:41.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是符合温室效应规律的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's exactly what we expect from greenhouse warming,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.76,0:24:44.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}与太阳输送能量的增加\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but the opposite of what increased solar output
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.03,0:24:46.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一点关系都没有\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.07,0:24:48.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}怀疑是没有用的 现在的一切清楚表明\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's now clear beyond any reasonable doubt
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.31,0:24:51.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人类正在改变气候\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we are changing the climate.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.04,0:24:53.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳根本就不是元凶\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun isn't the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.04,0:24:54.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而拯救这一切的方案\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it is the solution,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.88,0:24:57.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人类早已制备了很久\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we've known this for a long time,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.08,0:25:00.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}早在比你想象中更久远的年代\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}much longer than you might think.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.26,0:25:07.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}巴黎 1878年9月\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Paris, September 1878.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.83,0:25:12.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}埃菲尔铁塔还要过好多年才会开始建造\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Eiffel Tower won't be built for years to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.77,0:25:17.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.50,0:25:18.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}世博会
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.61,0:25:23.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}世界上最壮观非凡的景象\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the world has ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.64,0:25:26.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}自由女神像宏伟的头部\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The magnificent head of the Statue of Liberty
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.91,0:25:29.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}才刚刚造好\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has just been completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.59,0:25:37.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}全球各地数千家展商\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Thousands of exhibitors from around the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.86,0:25:40.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在巴黎的66英亩土地上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}covered 66 acres of Paris
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.09,0:25:42.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}布满了他们的发明与产品\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with their inventions and goods.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.40,0:25:45.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}爱迪生发明的灯泡还要在好几年后才\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Edison's first public demonstration of the light bulb
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.40,0:25:48.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}第一次向公众展示\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will not take place for another year.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.07,0:25:50.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}电气设备还没有出现\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's no such thing as electrical appliances.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.97,0:25:53.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人们还不会开开关 按按钮\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}People don't flick switches and press buttons.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.97,0:25:57.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是一个人牵马拉的世界\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's a hand-cranked, horse-drawn world.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.98,0:26:01.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是我们要说到的那个人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's the guy we came to see,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.65,0:26:04.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那个有奇怪胡子的人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the one with the crazy moustache.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.49,0:26:07.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他是一个数学老师 名叫奥古斯丁?莫超\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He's a math teacher named Augustin Mouchot.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.53,0:26:09.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}记住 这是在1878年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Remember, it's 1878.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.00,0:26:13.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一个由煤气灯统治的世界\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is a world lit mostly by gaslight.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.47,0:26:15.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}汽车还要过好多年才会发明\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The automobile is still years away.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.87,0:26:19.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但莫超的发明足以让观众目瞪口呆\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But Mouchot, here, is dazzling the crowd
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.67,0:26:21.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那是一个太阳能聚能设备\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with his solar power concentrator.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.68,0:26:26.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳属于我们每一个人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun belongs to all of us!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.98,0:26:31.15,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就算它距离我们1亿5千万公里远\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even though it is 150 million kilometers away from us,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.18,0:26:33.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}感受一下它那强悍的威力吧\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}feel its awesome power!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.35,0:26:37.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我的发明能把太阳散发的免费的能量集中起来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}My invention concentrates the free energy of the Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.36,0:26:40.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}把它转化为机械运动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and converts it into mechanical motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.36,0:26:42.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为任何一种机器提供能量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It can power any kind of machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.00,0:26:47.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它可以用来发电或者是让印刷机运转\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It can produce electricity or run a printing press
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.37,0:26:49.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}甚至是在热天制冰\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or make ice on a hot day.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.81,0:26:54.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}等着瞧吧\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Et voila !
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.38,0:27:06.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}想想吧\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.49,0:27:08.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}既然阳光能转化为冰块\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sunlight converted into ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.92,0:27:11.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}想想吧 朋友们 如果我们能把丰富的太阳能利用起来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You see, my friends, what wonders we can work
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.76,0:27:14.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们能做出什么样的奇迹来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if we harness the bounteous energy of the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.93,0:27:18.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}世界上的煤总有一天会用完\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The world will someday run out of coal,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.73,0:27:22.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但辉煌的太阳永远在那里照耀着我们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but the magnificent Sun will always be there for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.42,0:27:39.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}莫超获得了这一届世界博览会的金奖\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Mouchot took home the gold medal from the fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.92,0:27:41.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但煤炭的价格下跌了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the price of coal tumbled,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.75,0:27:45.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}价格如此之低以至于人们对太阳能再也没有兴趣\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}becoming so cheap that there was no interest in solar energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.26,0:27:47.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}此外 当时还没有人明白\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Besides, no one understood, back then,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.03,0:27:50.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}燃烧化石燃料的真正代价是什么\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what the true cost was of burning fossil fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.76,0:27:53.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}莫超的研究经费被砍掉了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Mouchot's research funding was cut off.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.93,0:27:58.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}35年后 也就是二十世纪初期\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}35 years later, in the early years of the 20th century,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.37,0:28:01.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}通向另一个未来的另一扇大门被打开了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}another door opened to an alternative future.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.04,0:28:05.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它发生在埃及 尼罗河岸边\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It happened in Egypt, on the banks of the Nile.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.81,0:28:17.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}未来的时间旅行者们记住了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Memo to future time travelers...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.81,0:28:20.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是一个对避免气候变化而言\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}this would be an excellent entry point
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.15,0:28:23.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}绝佳的起点\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for averting climate change.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.25,0:28:26.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1913年 埃及\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Egypt, 1913.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.26,0:28:29.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是来自美国费城的弗兰克?舒曼\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's Frank Shuman of Philadelphia.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.09,0:28:33.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他只读过3年书\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He's only had three years of schooling,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.43,0:28:38.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但他天才的创造发明能力弥补了这一切\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but his genius for innovation more than makes up for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.43,0:28:42.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在30岁以前 舒曼发明了安全玻璃\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Before he was 30, Shuman had invented safety glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.50,0:28:47.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它被广泛用在汽车与飞机上 挽救了无数的生命\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Its use in automobiles and skylights saved countless lives
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.34,0:28:49.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也让他变得非常有钱\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and made him a very rich man,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.68,0:28:53.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有钱 让他能去追求自己真正的梦想\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}rich enough to pursue his real passion,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.62,0:28:55.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳能\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}solar energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.85,0:28:58.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}舒曼领导着一支团队设计并建造了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Shuman led the team that designed and built
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.12,0:29:01.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一组太阳能聚能设备\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an array of solar energy concentrators.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.36,0:29:04.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它能驱动蒸汽机\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It could power a steam engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.86,0:29:08.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}舒曼希望利用太阳能\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Shuman is hoping to use the Sun's power
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.03,0:29:09.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以灌溉沙漠\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to irrigate the desert
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.63,0:29:11.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}让它重新变绿\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and turn it green.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.47,0:29:13.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}舒曼的太阳能发电站\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The official inauguration
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.10,0:29:16.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在1913年正式启动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of Shuman's solar power plant, in 1913,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.10,0:29:17.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是个了不起的成就\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was a dazzling success.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.14,0:29:24.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他发明了一种实用的方法\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He had invented a practical way to tap the Sun's energy
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.88,0:29:27.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}让太阳能得以实现工业规模的应用\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on an industrial scale,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.52,0:29:31.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}让太阳能比煤更便宜\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}making solar energy even cheaper than coal.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.29,0:29:35.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}英德两国政府\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The British and German governments
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.79,0:29:37.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}给予了舒曼慷慨的赞助\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}both offered Shuman generous funding
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.79,0:29:39.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}让他去创造发明\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to develop his invention.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.70,0:29:42.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是一种理想的丰富的能量来源\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was the ideal source of abundant power
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.73,0:29:44.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}尤其是在热带地区\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in tropical regions,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.73,0:29:48.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那里进口煤的价格比较昂贵\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where imported coal was prohibitively expensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.57,0:29:52.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但舒曼有更大的梦想\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But Shuman was dreaming even bigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.34,0:29:54.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在给《科学美国人》写的一封信中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In a letter to Scientific American,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.74,0:29:57.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他对他的太阳能发电厂进行了计算\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he calculated that his solar power plants,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.58,0:29:59.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果能将它安装在一个像撒哈拉沙漠那样的地区\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if deployed in an area of the Sahara Desert
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.92,0:30:03.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只需要方圆150英里的面积 就能提供\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}only 150 miles on a side, could supply as much power
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.99,0:30:07.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}足以让世界所有工厂消费的能量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as consumed by all the industries of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.16,0:30:09.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但这一切最终没有发生\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it was not to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.16,0:30:12.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}石油 这种液体化石燃料的市场\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The market for a liquid fossil fuel, petroleum,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.26,0:30:14.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}随船运而蓬勃发展起来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was exploding for shipping,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.10,0:30:16.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}家庭供热 汽车与卡车\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}home heating, and cars and trucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.73,0:30:19.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}石油很丰富 甚至比煤还便宜\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Oil was abundant, cheaper even than coal,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.40,0:30:22.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它很容易就能获得 易于加工\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and much easier to get out of the ground and process.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.31,0:30:26.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}要把煤装满一艘船 需要100个人干上1周\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It took 100 men a week to fuel a ship with coal,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.81,0:30:29.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但如果是装石油\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but with oil, one man could do the job
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.35,0:30:30.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1个人干上1天就可以了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in a single day.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.01,0:30:34.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}舒曼在沙漠中取得成功后的第2年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A year after Shuman's triumph in the desert,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.85,0:30:36.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}第一次世界大战爆发\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}World War I broke out.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.69,0:30:40.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他的太阳能集热器被回收 变成了武器\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}His solar collectors were recycled into weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.46,0:30:43.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}舒曼梦想中的太阳能发电的文明社会\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Frank Shuman's dream of a solar-powered civilization
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.53,0:30:46.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只有等到下一个世纪\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would have to wait another century
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.37,0:30:48.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}才能获得重生的机遇\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}before it was reborn.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.14,0:30:51.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在我们这个世界上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's another inexhaustible source of clean energy
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.57,0:30:53.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有另一种取之不尽的清洁能源\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.24,0:30:58.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}风能本身也是由太阳能产生的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The winds themselves are solar-powered,
